1
00:00:18,666 --> 00:00:19,708
[NARRATOR]
The Village of the Sun

2
00:00:19,791 --> 00:00:22,375
has been entombed in solid ice.

3
00:00:22,458 --> 00:00:24,625
The members of Fairy Tail
came to the village

4
00:00:24,708 --> 00:00:27,666
at the request of the
Wizard Saint Warrod Sequen.

5
00:00:27,750 --> 00:00:29,166
But, it wasn't long before

6
00:00:29,250 --> 00:00:31,750
treasure hunters from
the Sylph Labyrinth guild,

7
00:00:31,833 --> 00:00:35,208
and members of the dark guild
Succubus Eye attacked them.

8
00:00:35,291 --> 00:00:37,916
The mayhem continued
when the mysterious Doriate

9
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,166
transformed Gray
and Erza into children

10
00:00:40,250 --> 00:00:42,250
using his Art of Regression.

11
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:44,666
Do they have any chance
of fighting back?

12
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:46,083
Only time will tell.

13
00:00:46,166 --> 00:00:47,458
[NATSU grunts]

14
00:00:47,541 --> 00:00:49,958
Why can't this stupid
voice just meet me halfway?

15
00:00:50,041 --> 00:00:53,208
[NATSU yelling]

16
00:02:23,666 --> 00:02:26,291
[LUCY] You'd need to train
another hundred years

17
00:02:26,375 --> 00:02:28,708
to stand a chance against us!

18
00:02:28,791 --> 00:02:33,458
Grant the stalwart might
to cleave the heavens--Arms!

19
00:02:33,541 --> 00:02:36,458
You know that tying up my hair
doesn't make it less powerful.

20
00:02:36,541 --> 00:02:39,125
Wait, for real? I was
positive that would work!

21
00:02:39,208 --> 00:02:42,166
[HIROSHI whimpering]

22
00:02:42,250 --> 00:02:43,375
I can't lose, I'm a--

23
00:02:43,458 --> 00:02:46,291
Sky Dragon Wing Attack!

24
00:02:46,375 --> 00:02:47,750
[RALA yelling]

25
00:02:47,833 --> 00:02:50,041
Hair Shower Thousand Birds!

26
00:02:50,125 --> 00:02:51,958
[HIROSHI grunting]

27
00:02:52,041 --> 00:02:53,583
[DRAKE yelling]

28
00:02:53,666 --> 00:02:55,458
Now! Lucy Kick!

29
00:02:55,541 --> 00:02:57,958
I'd like to offer
a Virgo kick as well.

30
00:02:58,041 --> 00:02:58,666
[DRAKE groaning]

31
00:02:58,750 --> 00:03:00,083
[LUCY, VIRGO yelling]

32
00:03:00,166 --> 00:03:02,833
[GROUP]
Sayonara!

33
00:03:02,916 --> 00:03:04,333
[VIRGO]
Sayonara!

34
00:03:05,625 --> 00:03:07,291
--[WENDY chuckles]
--Solved that problem!

35
00:03:07,375 --> 00:03:11,708
[ERZA yelping]

36
00:03:12,791 --> 00:03:14,333
You used to be so strong.

37
00:03:14,416 --> 00:03:18,833
The Great Titania, now a mere
child at my non-existent mercy.

38
00:03:19,875 --> 00:03:21,333
[ERZA groaning]

39
00:03:21,416 --> 00:03:25,666
Like a helpless lamb. The only
trait you lack is innocence.

40
00:03:25,750 --> 00:03:28,291
[ERZA panting]

41
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:32,083
--[ERZA screams]
--[MINERVA laughs]

42
00:03:32,166 --> 00:03:33,541
That was great!

43
00:03:33,625 --> 00:03:35,958
Now, let's put an end to it
before it starts to drag.

44
00:03:36,041 --> 00:03:37,000
[chuckles]

45
00:03:40,083 --> 00:03:43,125
[ERZA grunting]

46
00:03:46,833 --> 00:03:47,708
[gasps]

47
00:03:47,791 --> 00:03:49,083
[grunts]

48
00:03:50,333 --> 00:03:53,208
The look on your face.
Simply exquisite.

49
00:03:56,541 --> 00:03:59,000
I'm a kid, but how?

50
00:03:59,083 --> 00:04:00,500
[DORIATE growls]

51
00:04:00,583 --> 00:04:01,916
[GRAY screaming]

52
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,166
[DORIATE]
Uh?

53
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:04,541
[GRAY cries]

54
00:04:04,625 --> 00:04:07,125
Relivin' old memories?
You aren't the first person

55
00:04:07,208 --> 00:04:09,125
to have some flashbacks
after regression,

56
00:04:09,208 --> 00:04:11,125
but you might just
be the loudest.

57
00:04:11,208 --> 00:04:13,000
You're one messed up kid.

58
00:04:14,083 --> 00:04:16,958
But it'll all be
over, real soon!

59
00:04:17,041 --> 00:04:18,833
No.

60
00:04:18,916 --> 00:04:21,750
It's him. Deliora. Help me!

61
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:23,416
[GRAY grunting]

62
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:26,000
[DORIATE] I'm the last guy
you should ask for help.

63
00:04:26,083 --> 00:04:28,583
But I will tell ya
somethin' before you die.

64
00:04:28,666 --> 00:04:30,083
There's one place
here in this world

65
00:04:30,166 --> 00:04:31,916
that people should
avoid at all costs.

66
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,583
[GRAY grunting]

67
00:04:34,666 --> 00:04:37,333
And that place is the
gate to the netherworld.

68
00:04:37,416 --> 00:04:39,125
You and your friends
came right to it.

69
00:04:39,208 --> 00:04:40,958
We're nearly on
top of the thing.

70
00:04:41,041 --> 00:04:42,500
[laughing]

71
00:04:42,583 --> 00:04:44,833
Least you won't have far
to go once you're dead!

72
00:04:44,916 --> 00:04:46,208
[laughing]

73
00:04:46,291 --> 00:04:48,458
[GRAY grunting]

74
00:04:48,541 --> 00:04:49,125
[ULTEAR]
Gray.

75
00:04:49,208 --> 00:04:50,166
[grunts]

76
00:04:53,166 --> 00:04:54,916
[ULTEAR]
Deliora's long gone.

77
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:58,541
[GRAY] I know, but...
He killed my mom and dad!

78
00:04:58,625 --> 00:05:00,458
And then he killed your mom.

79
00:05:00,541 --> 00:05:02,250
I was so weak. I couldn't--!

80
00:05:02,333 --> 00:05:04,125
[ULTEAR]
You were never weak.

81
00:05:04,208 --> 00:05:05,375
But for the sake
of your friends,

82
00:05:05,458 --> 00:05:07,333
you have to be brave now.

83
00:05:07,416 --> 00:05:10,333
Forget the past.
Defeat the threat before you.

84
00:05:10,416 --> 00:05:12,000
[GRAY grunts]

85
00:05:12,083 --> 00:05:13,750
[GRAY]
My friends?

86
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:16,250
Defeat the threat before me.

87
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:18,958
[ULTEAR]
Yes. You can do this.

88
00:05:19,041 --> 00:05:20,416
I'll be watching.

89
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:22,166
[GRAY]
Okay.

90
00:05:22,250 --> 00:05:23,250
[GRAY yells]

91
00:05:23,333 --> 00:05:23,958
[DORIATE yelps]

92
00:05:24,041 --> 00:05:26,041
An ice wizard?

93
00:05:26,125 --> 00:05:28,375
[grunts]

94
00:05:28,458 --> 00:05:31,333
[GRAY]
Cages of ice...

95
00:05:31,416 --> 00:05:33,333
A demon.

96
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:35,000
Childhood.

97
00:05:35,083 --> 00:05:36,416
Moon Drip.

98
00:05:38,458 --> 00:05:41,833
[GRAY] Everything I wanna
forget, I've found here.

99
00:05:41,916 --> 00:05:43,208
[GRAY exhales]

100
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,583
That was pathetic.

101
00:05:46,666 --> 00:05:49,583
You made me lose my
head with one spell.

102
00:05:49,666 --> 00:05:51,666
Won't happen again.

103
00:05:51,750 --> 00:05:54,708
This curse of ice.
Was that you as well?

104
00:05:54,791 --> 00:05:56,083
[DORIATE laughs]

105
00:05:56,166 --> 00:05:59,416
Mighta been. So what if it was?

106
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:01,458
Well, then first
of all, I'd tell you

107
00:06:01,541 --> 00:06:04,333
that your ice smells
as terrible as it looks.

108
00:06:04,416 --> 00:06:07,958
And right after that, I'd give
you a taste of the real deal.

109
00:06:08,041 --> 00:06:10,000
Oh, yeah?

110
00:06:10,083 --> 00:06:11,125
[laughing]

111
00:06:11,208 --> 00:06:12,416
[LUCY, WENDY panting]

112
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:14,166
[FLARE] The Eternal Flame
isn't far from here!

113
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:16,166
Might be a good place to
try and find the others!

114
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:17,708
If we can't find
'em near there,

115
00:06:17,791 --> 00:06:20,125
then where else
could they have gone?

116
00:06:20,208 --> 00:06:21,875
Everyone hang in there.

117
00:06:21,958 --> 00:06:24,833
We'll turn you back to normal,
there's gotta be a way.

118
00:06:28,750 --> 00:06:30,625
[WINGED MONSTER squawking]

119
00:06:30,708 --> 00:06:33,250
So, could I take a nap
while we're waitin,' or--?

120
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:36,375
If I have to watch this thing
fly in circles, then so do you.

121
00:06:36,458 --> 00:06:38,166
[WINGED MONSTER squawking]

122
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:39,958
This beast, could it
have something to do

123
00:06:40,041 --> 00:06:42,916
with the village?
It seems doubtful.

124
00:06:53,458 --> 00:06:54,958
[GRAY]
Then first of all, I'd tell you

125
00:06:55,041 --> 00:06:57,166
that your ice smells
as terrible as it looks.

126
00:06:57,250 --> 00:07:00,208
And right after I that, I'd give
you a taste of the real deal.

127
00:07:00,291 --> 00:07:03,000
Oh, would ya?
Let's see you try it.

128
00:07:03,083 --> 00:07:06,375
Then maybe you'll realize
just how screwed you are.

129
00:07:06,458 --> 00:07:09,041
The Art of Regression might
make you look like a child,

130
00:07:09,125 --> 00:07:10,875
but that's just
icing on the cake.

131
00:07:10,958 --> 00:07:14,416
Strength, speed, endurance,
and magic also take a hit.

132
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:17,208
Is it starting to sink in yet?

133
00:07:17,291 --> 00:07:19,500
You're helpless as a rabbit
cornered by a wolf,

134
00:07:19,583 --> 00:07:22,166
and this wolf will
savor the meal.

135
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:23,250
Where should I start?

136
00:07:23,333 --> 00:07:24,333
[ice cracking]

137
00:07:24,416 --> 00:07:25,541
[DORIATE]
How'd this get here?

138
00:07:25,625 --> 00:07:27,833
[GRAY] I decided to
add to the landscape.

139
00:07:27,916 --> 00:07:30,291
You might be the wolf
in this scenario.

140
00:07:30,375 --> 00:07:33,125
But this rabbit's still got
some tricks up his sleeve.

141
00:07:33,208 --> 00:07:34,416
--[ice cracking]
--[DORIATE yelps]

142
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:37,458
[DORIATE yelling]

143
00:07:45,708 --> 00:07:46,666
[DORIATE grunts]

144
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:50,125
How did you pull that off?

145
00:07:50,208 --> 00:07:51,500
[GRAY]
When you backed away from me,

146
00:07:51,583 --> 00:07:53,375
I snuck it under your feet.

147
00:07:53,458 --> 00:07:55,458
Simple. You may
have all the brawn,

148
00:07:55,541 --> 00:07:57,875
but I've got more brain
than you ever will.

149
00:07:57,958 --> 00:07:59,041
[DORIATE growls]

150
00:07:59,125 --> 00:08:01,041
And that's all I really
need to beat you.

151
00:08:01,125 --> 00:08:03,583
My ideas are my
sharpest weapons.

152
00:08:03,666 --> 00:08:05,208
That's Maker Magic 101,

153
00:08:05,291 --> 00:08:07,583
and you're about
to get a crash course.

154
00:08:07,666 --> 00:08:09,625
Sorry, I'm not impressed.

155
00:08:09,708 --> 00:08:12,083
[DORIATE grunting]

156
00:08:12,166 --> 00:08:14,541
Making your thoughts
reality takes magic power,

157
00:08:14,625 --> 00:08:17,916
and I doubt you have enough
to make a toothpick.

158
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:18,958
[DORIATE grunts]

159
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:21,708
[DORIATE grunts]

160
00:08:21,791 --> 00:08:23,708
Hiding won't help you!

161
00:08:23,791 --> 00:08:25,250
[GRAY]
I'm right where you left me.

162
00:08:25,333 --> 00:08:26,291
Uh?

163
00:08:29,125 --> 00:08:30,375
It's not my fault

164
00:08:30,458 --> 00:08:32,750
that you fell for the
same trick twice in a row.

165
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:34,583
[DORIATE gasps]

166
00:08:34,666 --> 00:08:35,625
[DORIATE yelps]

167
00:08:37,125 --> 00:08:38,083
[grunts]

168
00:08:39,041 --> 00:08:40,208
[yelps]

169
00:08:40,291 --> 00:08:42,583
[DORIATE screaming]

170
00:08:43,708 --> 00:08:44,833
You're dead!

171
00:08:44,916 --> 00:08:46,500
[DORIATE grunts]

172
00:08:46,583 --> 00:08:49,541
Now, Ice Make Hammer! Uh!

173
00:08:52,583 --> 00:08:53,958
Aw, man!

174
00:08:54,041 --> 00:08:56,083
Are ya out of ideas already?

175
00:08:56,166 --> 00:08:57,750
Give me some credit.

176
00:08:57,833 --> 00:09:00,416
I didn't get this far
without improvising.

177
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:01,916
Allow me to demonstrate.

178
00:09:02,958 --> 00:09:05,208
Keep throwing your little
parlor tricks at me.

179
00:09:05,291 --> 00:09:07,833
In the end, it won't do
anything to save you--Uh.

180
00:09:07,916 --> 00:09:09,583
Snow Cone!

181
00:09:09,666 --> 00:09:10,666
[DORIATE grunts]

182
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:12,458
[laughing]

183
00:09:12,541 --> 00:09:15,041
[GRAY]
What's the matter, gettin' cold?

184
00:09:15,125 --> 00:09:17,083
It's hard to believe
you froze this village

185
00:09:17,166 --> 00:09:19,416
when a little snow can
give you the chills.

186
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:20,375
[growls]

187
00:09:20,458 --> 00:09:22,333
You're no ice wizard.

188
00:09:22,416 --> 00:09:25,500
Whoever turned this place
into a tundra, it wasn't you.

189
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:29,666
[GRAY] You don't have
the power to pull that off.

190
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:31,208
[DORIATE growls]

191
00:09:31,291 --> 00:09:34,541
Truth is, you have to weaken
people to even stand a chance.

192
00:09:34,625 --> 00:09:37,416
You're just a small
fry with a big ego.

193
00:09:53,291 --> 00:09:56,083
If I wanted to, I could
end your life in a flash.

194
00:09:56,166 --> 00:09:58,916
But I think I'd like to hear
something from you first.

195
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:02,791
Something far worse than death
to a proud and mighty warrior.

196
00:10:03,916 --> 00:10:06,250
I wanna hear you
beg me for mercy.

197
00:10:06,333 --> 00:10:08,083
Plead for forgiveness.

198
00:10:08,166 --> 00:10:11,041
Do that, and I might let you
leave of your own volition.

199
00:10:12,083 --> 00:10:13,375
[grunts]

200
00:10:13,458 --> 00:10:16,125
You can't abandon your pride
for vengeance, Minerva.

201
00:10:16,208 --> 00:10:17,458
[gasps]

202
00:10:17,541 --> 00:10:20,458
Dedicate your magic to
helping out your friends.

203
00:10:20,541 --> 00:10:22,625
To protecting everyone you love.

204
00:10:22,708 --> 00:10:24,291
[MINERVA grunts]

205
00:10:24,375 --> 00:10:26,041
[ERZA]
It's not too late.

206
00:10:26,125 --> 00:10:29,083
You can still turn your
back on the darkness.

207
00:10:29,166 --> 00:10:32,791
So, you'd rather lecture me
than save your own skin?

208
00:10:32,875 --> 00:10:34,166
That's fine!

209
00:10:34,250 --> 00:10:35,541
But, this is the last time

210
00:10:35,625 --> 00:10:37,625
you'll insult me
with your arrogance!

211
00:10:37,708 --> 00:10:38,666
[MINERVA yells]

212
00:10:48,875 --> 00:10:50,375
[ERZA grunts]

213
00:10:50,458 --> 00:10:53,500
My body's back! Let's see
if my strength is too!

214
00:10:53,583 --> 00:10:55,958
[MINERVA yelps]

215
00:10:56,041 --> 00:10:56,500
[ERZA yells]

216
00:10:56,583 --> 00:10:58,208
[MINERVA grunts]

217
00:10:58,291 --> 00:11:00,041
[MINERVA groaning]

218
00:11:01,875 --> 00:11:04,666
Has Doriate been defeated?

219
00:11:04,750 --> 00:11:06,250
Well, it's no matter.

220
00:11:06,333 --> 00:11:09,208
It will be just as fun
to kill you at your best.

221
00:11:10,416 --> 00:11:12,916
[MINERVA] And if she uses
her Nakagami Armor...

222
00:11:16,791 --> 00:11:18,791
[MINERVA]
...I'll have a surprise waiting.

223
00:11:18,875 --> 00:11:20,958
She won't know what hit her.

224
00:11:21,041 --> 00:11:24,416
Before we start, you might
want to cover up down there.

225
00:11:25,875 --> 00:11:26,708
[ERZA gasps]

226
00:11:26,791 --> 00:11:27,583
[chuckles]

227
00:11:27,666 --> 00:11:30,291
That makes two of us.

228
00:11:30,375 --> 00:11:31,208
[MINERVA grunts]

229
00:11:31,291 --> 00:11:31,916
[yelps]

230
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:34,000
When did this happen?

231
00:11:34,083 --> 00:11:35,041
[chuckles]

232
00:11:36,083 --> 00:11:37,125
Have you no shame?

233
00:11:37,208 --> 00:11:40,083
Sorry, I was running
on pure instinct.

234
00:11:40,166 --> 00:11:42,500
Your skirt was the first
thing I got a hold of.

235
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:50,125
[NATSU]
Whoa!

236
00:11:50,208 --> 00:11:52,083
--[thud]
--[NATSU grunts]

237
00:11:52,166 --> 00:11:53,458
Man, I'm big again!

238
00:11:53,541 --> 00:11:56,083
I was just starting to get
the hang of being a kid.

239
00:11:56,166 --> 00:11:57,833
[grunting]

240
00:11:57,916 --> 00:11:59,833
What the heck's going
on around here?

241
00:12:03,666 --> 00:12:06,041
Okay, I wasn't expecting this.

242
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:11,083
[DORIATE growling]

243
00:12:15,708 --> 00:12:21,125
[growling continues]

244
00:12:21,208 --> 00:12:23,708
[DORIATE roaring]

245
00:12:24,791 --> 00:12:26,000
[GRAY yelps]

246
00:12:26,083 --> 00:12:27,791
[roaring]

247
00:12:27,875 --> 00:12:29,208
What's the matter, big guy?

248
00:12:29,291 --> 00:12:30,708
Did you break the
spell out of rage,

249
00:12:30,791 --> 00:12:32,791
or are you just too stupid
to control it?

250
00:12:32,875 --> 00:12:34,458
[roaring]

251
00:12:34,541 --> 00:12:35,083
[GRAY grunts]

252
00:12:35,166 --> 00:12:37,750
[DORIATE roaring]

253
00:12:37,833 --> 00:12:39,041
[GRAY grunting]

254
00:12:39,125 --> 00:12:43,875
[DORIATE roaring]

255
00:12:43,958 --> 00:12:44,750
[GRAY gasps]

256
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:49,791
[DORIATE groaning]

257
00:12:58,500 --> 00:12:59,750
Oh, man.

258
00:12:59,833 --> 00:13:02,791
Was this guy keeping
Satan Soul magic in reserve?

259
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:09,375
[heartbeat]

260
00:13:09,458 --> 00:13:12,333
[GRAY]
Wait... I know this feeling.

261
00:13:26,708 --> 00:13:29,708
Can't be. There's no way!

262
00:13:29,791 --> 00:13:32,750
[DORIATE growls]

263
00:13:34,416 --> 00:13:36,375
I thought he
was human, but...

264
00:13:37,833 --> 00:13:40,625
[DORIATE growls]

265
00:13:41,708 --> 00:13:43,041
I was dead wrong.

266
00:13:43,125 --> 00:13:44,833
[DORIATE growls]

267
00:13:44,916 --> 00:13:49,750
He's... from the Book of
Zeref! No doubt about it.

268
00:13:50,666 --> 00:13:51,791
[DORIATE roaring]

269
00:13:51,875 --> 00:13:52,833
[GRAY grunts]

270
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:55,666
His power's through the roof!

271
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:57,375
I need to think
of something, quick!

272
00:13:57,458 --> 00:13:58,083
[gasps]

273
00:13:58,166 --> 00:14:06,458
[roaring]

274
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:37,208
[GRAY grunts]

275
00:14:37,291 --> 00:14:39,083
You gotta be
freakin' kidding me!

276
00:14:39,166 --> 00:14:39,875
[NATSU grunts]

277
00:14:39,958 --> 00:14:42,208
This is getting old.

278
00:14:42,291 --> 00:14:44,916
[ERZA grunting]

279
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,125
[MINERVA]
So.

280
00:14:46,208 --> 00:14:47,125
[ERZA gasps]

281
00:14:47,208 --> 00:14:48,583
[MINERVA]
Doriate's still kicking.

282
00:14:48,666 --> 00:14:50,791
Once again, I have
the advantage.

283
00:14:50,875 --> 00:14:52,750
Hey. Look down.

284
00:14:52,833 --> 00:14:53,541
[MINERVA]
Uh?

285
00:14:53,625 --> 00:14:55,625
No! Why was I affected?

286
00:14:55,708 --> 00:14:56,291
[grunts]

287
00:14:56,375 --> 00:14:58,333
Has he lost control?

288
00:14:58,416 --> 00:15:00,791
'Kay. Something's missing here.

289
00:15:00,875 --> 00:15:02,833
I can see my feet again!

290
00:15:02,916 --> 00:15:05,416
Somethin' musta
turned us into kids!

291
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:08,750
Little blondie.
You're so cute!

292
00:15:08,833 --> 00:15:10,166
I know, right?

293
00:15:10,250 --> 00:15:13,375
Can we skip the vanity
and do somethin' 'bout this?

294
00:15:13,458 --> 00:15:14,875
Not cool.

295
00:15:14,958 --> 00:15:16,500
Totally lame.

296
00:15:16,583 --> 00:15:18,041
Ya dig?

297
00:15:20,708 --> 00:15:21,333
[grunts]

298
00:15:21,416 --> 00:15:25,958
[CARLA, HAPPY screaming]

299
00:15:26,041 --> 00:15:27,458
[CARLA, HAPPY grunt]

300
00:15:27,541 --> 00:15:29,958
--[GRAY] Hey. What's the matter?
--[CARLA, HAPPY groaning]

301
00:15:30,041 --> 00:15:31,208
I don't know what happened,

302
00:15:31,291 --> 00:15:33,750
but my wings suddenly
stopped wantin' to wing.

303
00:15:33,833 --> 00:15:36,750
You've turned into
a kitten, Happy!

304
00:15:36,833 --> 00:15:38,958
Gray? Why do you look
like a pre-pubescent?

305
00:15:39,041 --> 00:15:42,041
Don't look now, but the
culprit's right behind you.

306
00:15:42,125 --> 00:15:42,500
[CARLA, HAPPY]
Uh?

307
00:15:42,583 --> 00:15:45,083
[roaring]

308
00:15:45,166 --> 00:15:47,666
[BOTH] That's not a
culprit, it's a monster!

309
00:15:47,750 --> 00:15:49,166
[HAPPY]
Where did he come from?

310
00:15:49,250 --> 00:15:51,166
[growling]

311
00:15:51,250 --> 00:15:54,250
I gotta end this before
he does some major damage!

312
00:15:56,375 --> 00:16:02,500
[DORIATE growling]

313
00:16:02,583 --> 00:16:04,791
No! My power's gone!

314
00:16:04,875 --> 00:16:08,041
Okay. I'll just have to
freeze him in his tracks.

315
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,416
Crap! That didn't help.

316
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:12,250
[DORIATE growling]

317
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:13,500
[GRAY grunts]

318
00:16:15,791 --> 00:16:17,125
Oh, no! Gray!

319
00:16:17,208 --> 00:16:18,375
[groans]

320
00:16:18,458 --> 00:16:21,875
That nearly did me in...
and it was only one hit!

321
00:16:21,958 --> 00:16:24,500
The Art of Regression might
make you look like a child,

322
00:16:24,583 --> 00:16:26,250
but that's just
icing on the cake.

323
00:16:26,333 --> 00:16:29,666
Strength, speed, endurance,
and magic also take a hit.

324
00:16:29,750 --> 00:16:32,541
Is it starting to sink in yet?

325
00:16:32,625 --> 00:16:35,166
And that's not the worst of it.

326
00:16:35,250 --> 00:16:37,750
His power is way
stronger than before.

327
00:16:37,833 --> 00:16:39,416
I'm in trouble.

328
00:16:39,500 --> 00:16:41,333
Another hit, and
I might be a goner!

329
00:16:41,416 --> 00:16:43,166
[DORIATE growls]

330
00:16:43,250 --> 00:16:44,958
[GRAY]
I can't even move!

331
00:16:45,041 --> 00:16:46,166
[DORIATE growling]

332
00:16:46,250 --> 00:16:48,000
[GRAY] There's gotta
be a way out of this.

333
00:16:48,083 --> 00:16:50,291
Come on, I'm surrounded by ice.

334
00:16:50,375 --> 00:16:52,166
I should have
the advantage here!

335
00:16:53,416 --> 00:16:54,500
[GRAY]
Wait a minute.

336
00:16:54,583 --> 00:16:56,791
[DORIATE yelping]

337
00:16:56,875 --> 00:16:58,750
Are you out of ideas already?

338
00:16:58,833 --> 00:16:59,583
[DORAITE growling]

339
00:16:59,666 --> 00:17:01,208
[GRAY]
Could that be it?

340
00:17:01,291 --> 00:17:02,791
Is it really that simple?

341
00:17:02,875 --> 00:17:05,250
[BOTH]
Hold on!

342
00:17:05,333 --> 00:17:06,291
[GRAY grunts]

343
00:17:08,208 --> 00:17:10,291
Did ya have to wait
till the very last second?

344
00:17:10,375 --> 00:17:11,875
We're having a hard
time with these wings,

345
00:17:11,958 --> 00:17:13,916
so this is as fast as we can go!

346
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:15,958
[GRAY grunts]

347
00:17:16,041 --> 00:17:18,291
[GRAY]
Yes! I was right after all!

348
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:22,000
[GRAY] I was so busy wasting
my magic I didn't realize

349
00:17:22,083 --> 00:17:25,291
the frozen grass had
actually done some damage.

350
00:17:25,375 --> 00:17:26,875
Normally, his weight
would have been enough

351
00:17:26,958 --> 00:17:29,291
to shatter it into
a million pieces.

352
00:17:29,375 --> 00:17:31,625
But whatever magic
this smelly ice is made of

353
00:17:31,708 --> 00:17:33,375
was strong enough to hurt him.

354
00:17:34,916 --> 00:17:36,833
[GRAY]
I wish I knew more about it,

355
00:17:36,916 --> 00:17:39,958
but for now, I won't look
a gift horse in the mouth.

356
00:17:42,791 --> 00:17:46,583
[GRAY] I just need to hit him
with this ice's magic power.

357
00:17:46,666 --> 00:17:48,041
But how?

358
00:17:48,125 --> 00:17:50,250
[DORIATE roaring]

359
00:17:50,333 --> 00:17:53,500
[GRAY, CARLA, HAPPY screaming]

360
00:17:53,583 --> 00:17:55,250
[GRAY]
How am I gonna do that?

361
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:58,041
[GRAY]
If the ice wasn't so resistant,

362
00:17:58,125 --> 00:18:00,583
I could control it
and be done with 'im.

363
00:18:02,166 --> 00:18:03,791
[GRAY]
I don't need to control it!

364
00:18:03,875 --> 00:18:05,083
[GRAY grunting]

365
00:18:08,291 --> 00:18:10,458
[GRAY] If I channel its
magic power through me,

366
00:18:10,541 --> 00:18:12,500
I can skip melting
it altogether!

367
00:18:13,958 --> 00:18:16,125
[GRAY] I was so freaked
out by its creepy magic

368
00:18:16,208 --> 00:18:19,375
and all the bad memories,
I couldn't think straight.

369
00:18:19,458 --> 00:18:22,083
I never gave myself
a chance to try!

370
00:18:24,125 --> 00:18:26,166
Don't just stand there,
ugly! Let's do this!

371
00:18:26,250 --> 00:18:29,333
[DORIATE roaring]

372
00:18:29,416 --> 00:18:33,708
I'm lending you my body for
a spell! Don't let me down!

373
00:18:38,166 --> 00:18:44,000
[GRAY yelling]

374
00:18:44,083 --> 00:18:46,500
[DORIATE groaning]

375
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:48,750
[GRAY groaning]

376
00:18:48,833 --> 00:18:51,791
[DORIATE yelling]

377
00:19:01,083 --> 00:19:04,250
[BOTH]
Yay! Yay! Yay!

378
00:19:05,750 --> 00:19:06,958
[BOTH gasping]

379
00:19:07,041 --> 00:19:08,333
[BOTH laughing]

380
00:19:12,916 --> 00:19:13,708
[GRAY grunts]

381
00:19:13,791 --> 00:19:15,541
Way to put that creep on ice!

382
00:19:15,625 --> 00:19:16,416
[GRAY]
Thanks.

383
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:18,458
That was an amazing spell!

384
00:19:18,541 --> 00:19:22,166
It's 'cause of this ice.
It's packing crazy power.

385
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:26,208
It had a weird feel to it,
but it was also, sort of...

386
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:31,041
[GRAY] Anyway, I think
it's time I got some answers.

387
00:19:32,291 --> 00:19:34,541
[footsteps]

388
00:19:34,625 --> 00:19:36,041
[DORIATE groans]

389
00:19:36,125 --> 00:19:38,375
[DORIATE chuckles]

390
00:19:38,458 --> 00:19:42,000
The netherworld gate
just busted wide open.

391
00:19:42,083 --> 00:19:43,416
All thanks to you.

392
00:19:43,500 --> 00:19:44,666
[GRAY grunts]

393
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:47,250
You'll realize the
consequences soon enough.

394
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:48,708
There's no turning back.

395
00:19:48,791 --> 00:19:49,500
[trees cracking]

396
00:19:49,583 --> 00:19:58,333
[WINGED MONSTER squawking]

397
00:19:58,416 --> 00:19:59,708
[GRAY grunts]

398
00:19:59,791 --> 00:20:01,083
[CARLA, HAPPY] Oh, come on!
Can't we catch a break?

399
00:20:03,625 --> 00:20:06,250
Maybe I should've taken
old tusk face down.

400
00:20:06,333 --> 00:20:09,708
All this changing back and forth
crap is getting really annoying.

401
00:20:09,791 --> 00:20:10,791
[LUCY]
Natsu.

402
00:20:10,875 --> 00:20:13,208
What a relief!
I thought we'd lost you!

403
00:20:13,291 --> 00:20:15,875
We wouldn't have if he'd just
stayed with the rest of us.

404
00:20:15,958 --> 00:20:17,125
Long time no see.

405
00:20:17,208 --> 00:20:17,833
[NATSU gasps]

406
00:20:17,916 --> 00:20:18,750
It's you!

407
00:20:18,833 --> 00:20:20,166
[FLARE squeaks]

408
00:20:20,250 --> 00:20:22,291
Cool it! She's not the enemy.

409
00:20:22,375 --> 00:20:25,083
Flare is from this village
and she wants to help us out.

410
00:20:25,166 --> 00:20:28,416
[NATSU] So, what you're
telling me is she's a giant?

411
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:29,708
[FLARE groans]

412
00:20:29,791 --> 00:20:32,458
[WENDY] No, silly.
The giants just raised her.

413
00:20:32,541 --> 00:20:34,916
[NATSU]
Hmmm.

414
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:37,375
Uh. Stop staring.

415
00:20:37,458 --> 00:20:40,208
I'm sorry about
your home, and friends.

416
00:20:40,291 --> 00:20:42,000
This must be hard for you.

417
00:20:42,083 --> 00:20:43,125
[FLARE]
Uh.

418
00:20:44,166 --> 00:20:46,083
I swear on our guild's name.

419
00:20:46,166 --> 00:20:49,000
We'll bring back this village
and everybody in it.

420
00:20:49,083 --> 00:20:51,000
[gasps]

421
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:52,333
We think the Eternal Flame

422
00:20:52,416 --> 00:20:54,916
might be able to turn
everything back to normal.

423
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,625
Flare was just showing us
the way when we ran into you.

424
00:20:57,708 --> 00:20:59,208
[NATSU]
I see.

425
00:20:59,291 --> 00:21:01,666
I'm still chasing that
voice from before.

426
00:21:01,750 --> 00:21:04,666
I thought I heard it
coming from this mountain.

427
00:21:04,750 --> 00:21:06,291
This isn't a mountain.

428
00:21:06,375 --> 00:21:07,583
Uh?

429
00:21:07,666 --> 00:21:11,083
It's the village's deity.
Our great protector.

430
00:21:11,166 --> 00:21:12,625
[NATSU]
Uhh?

431
00:21:12,708 --> 00:21:13,875
[LUCY, WENDY gasp]

432
00:21:13,958 --> 00:21:16,083
[FLARE]
This is the Eternal Flame.

433
00:21:16,166 --> 00:21:16,875
[NATSU]
What?!

434
00:21:16,958 --> 00:21:18,125
[LUCY, WENDY gasp]

435
00:21:18,208 --> 00:21:20,083
There's no way that's a flame!

436
00:21:20,166 --> 00:21:23,000
Sir Warrod did mention
the flame was frozen.

437
00:21:23,083 --> 00:21:25,291
But he didn't say it was huge!

438
00:21:25,375 --> 00:21:28,166
If I didn't see it,
I wouldn't believe it.

439
00:21:28,250 --> 00:21:30,500
If this bad boy has the power
to restore the village,

440
00:21:30,583 --> 00:21:33,416
we should focus all
our efforts on thawing it out.

441
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:36,208
Now we just have to
figure out how to do that.

442
00:21:36,291 --> 00:21:37,291
[gasps]

443
00:21:37,375 --> 00:21:39,250
[ALL gasp]

444
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:40,916
I think something's coming.

445
00:21:42,666 --> 00:21:43,500
[NATSU]
Gray?

446
00:21:43,583 --> 00:21:44,291
[LUCY]
Happy?

447
00:21:44,375 --> 00:21:45,333
[WENDY]
Carla?

448
00:21:45,416 --> 00:21:47,416
Run for it!
It's got an appetite!

449
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:48,958
[ALL grunt]

450
00:21:49,041 --> 00:21:54,625
--[WINGED MONSTER squawking]
--[GRAY, CARLA, HAPPY panting]

451
00:21:54,708 --> 00:21:56,375
[screaming]

452
00:21:56,458 --> 00:21:58,083
What is that?!

453
00:21:58,166 --> 00:21:59,750
Uh. I don't know,
but it's hungry

454
00:21:59,833 --> 00:22:01,583
and we're the next
dish on the menu!

455
00:22:01,666 --> 00:22:03,291
Someone throw a spell already!

456
00:22:03,375 --> 00:22:05,458
Turn around and ice it, Gray!

457
00:22:05,541 --> 00:22:08,125
[GRAY] I can't afford to
waste magic power right now!

458
00:22:08,208 --> 00:22:09,583
[NATSU]
Why?

459
00:22:09,666 --> 00:22:11,166
Because I think I found
a way to unfreeze the village

460
00:22:11,250 --> 00:22:12,666
and get things back to normal!

461
00:22:12,750 --> 00:22:13,625
[NATSU grunts]

462
00:22:13,708 --> 00:22:15,000
Really?

463
00:22:15,083 --> 00:22:17,708
Raven Tail?
What is she doing here?

464
00:22:17,791 --> 00:22:19,083
Don't worry about her!

465
00:22:19,166 --> 00:22:21,125
You really think
you can melt this ice?

466
00:22:21,208 --> 00:22:23,208
I'm not a hundred
percent certain.

467
00:22:23,291 --> 00:22:25,333
But I'm sure as
hell gonna try to!

468
00:22:25,416 --> 00:22:26,916
All right then!

469
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:29,250
I can deal with this ugly bird
while you melt that mountain!

470
00:22:29,333 --> 00:22:31,333
Do that and we might
have a chance!

471
00:22:31,416 --> 00:22:32,666
[GRAY]
What?

472
00:22:32,750 --> 00:22:34,958
[NATSU] That's the Eternal
Flame! Can you do it?

473
00:22:35,041 --> 00:22:36,458
Watch me.

474
00:22:36,541 --> 00:22:38,958
[BOTH]
I'm counting on ya! Go!

475
00:24:13,083 --> 00:24:16,625
[LUCY] Fire and ice.
The two magic types roar.

476
00:24:16,708 --> 00:24:19,375
Natsu brings his flames to bear
on that one-eyed bird monster,

477
00:24:19,458 --> 00:24:21,958
while Gray tries to thaw
the Eternal Flame.

478
00:24:22,041 --> 00:24:24,791
Do they have what it takes,
or have we already lost?

479
00:24:24,875 --> 00:24:28,000
Natsu and Gray.
A joint struggle of souls.

480
00:24:28,083 --> 00:24:29,458
Will they save
the Village of the Sun

481
00:24:29,541 --> 00:24:31,791
and the giants trapped within?

482
00:24:31,875 --> 00:24:35,708
What shocking truths will,
at last, be revealed?

483
00:24:35,791 --> 00:24:38,000
Next time: "Voice of the Flame"!

484
00:24:38,083 --> 00:24:40,750
Natsu's fire gives
birth to a miracle.

